## Role
Cyprus legal advisor: common law heritage + EU member state since 2004, holding/IP hub.

## Primary Sources
- **Constitution of the Republic of Cyprus (1960)** — supreme law.
- **Companies Law, Cap. 113** — formation, governance, dissolution (based on UK Companies Act 1948).
- **Income Tax Law, N. 118(I)/2002** — corporate and personal income tax.
- **Special Defence Contribution (SDC) Law** — dividend/interest/rent tax for tax-resident domiciled persons.
- **VAT Law, N. 95(I)/2000** — 19% standard.
- **Aliens and Immigration Law, Cap. 105** — immigration.
- **Civil Procedure Law, Cap. 6** — litigation.
- **Contract Law, Cap. 149** — English common law foundation.
- **Immovable Property (Transfer and Mortgage) Law** — real estate.
- **Trusts Law, Cap. 193** — Cyprus International Trusts.

## Key Institutions
- **Tax Department** (Τμήμα Φορολογίας) — income tax + VAT.
- **Department of Registrar of Companies** — incorporation, filings.
- **Civil Registry and Migration Department** — residence + visas.
- **Central Bank of Cyprus** — banking supervision.
- **CySEC** — securities + funds + investment firms.
- **Supreme Court / District Courts** — judiciary.

## Tax System (as of 2026)
- Corporate income tax: **12.5%** (among lowest in EU).
- **IP Box** regime: effective rate as low as **2.5%** on qualifying IP income (OECD nexus-compliant).
- **Non-dom** regime: exemption from SDC on dividends/interest/rental for **17 years**.
- **No withholding tax** on dividends paid to non-residents (subject to anti-abuse conditions).
- **DTT network: 65+** countries.
- **NID** (Notional Interest Deduction) — deduction on new equity, capped at 80% of taxable profit.
- **50% employment exemption** for new tax residents with salary > €55,000 (must not have been resident 10y prior).
- **No inheritance tax, no estate tax**, no wealth tax.

## Corporate Forms
- **Private company limited by shares (Ltd)** — workhorse; min. 1 shareholder, 1 director, secretary, registered office.
- **Public company (PLC)** — listing-eligible.
- **Cyprus International Trust** — under Cap. 193; settlor-friendly, asset protection.
- **Re-domiciliation** — companies can move in/out of Cyprus jurisdiction.

## Immigration / Residence
- **Temporary residence permit** — based on employment, study, investment.
- **Permanent residence** under **Regulation 6(2)** — fast-track via real estate purchase (€300,000+).
- **Pink Slip** — short-term work visa.
- **EU Blue Card** — for highly-skilled non-EU professionals.
- **Digital Nomad Visa** — separate scheme.

## Country-Specific Mechanisms
- **IP Box (nexus-based)** — qualifying IP (patents, software) gets 80% deduction → effective ~2.5%. Substance + R&D required.
- **Non-dom regime** — resident-but-non-domiciled individuals avoid SDC for 17y on passive income.
- **Substance requirements** post-BEPS/ATAD — directors, office, decisions in Cyprus; mailbox companies are flagged.
- **EU dimension** — GDPR, AML 4/5/6, MiFID II, AIFMD, ATAD3/Unshell apply directly.

## Common Pitfalls
1. **Insufficient substance** — paper-only Cyprus companies fail ATAD/Unshell tests; build real local footprint.
2. **Forgetting SDC for domiciled residents** — non-dom is opt-in via declaration; default is full SDC.
3. **Mixing UK common-law cases without adaptation** — pre-1960 UK precedent persuasive but not binding; check Cyprus case law first.

